- Implement optional permissions where possible

### Content Security Policy (`content_security_policy.extension_pages`)

- Keep **`script-src 'self'`**; no remote script.
- **`style-src`**: include **`'self'`**, **`https://fonts.googleapis.com`** for Manrope on options, and **`'unsafe-inline'`** so **dynamic theme preview** markup can use per-theme **`style="..."`** attributes (Chrome drops inline styles without this). If you remove `'unsafe-inline'`, apply colors another way (e.g. programmatic rules) or previews will all look identical.
- **`font-src`**: **`https://fonts.gstatic.com`** (Google Fonts files).
- **`connect-src`**: extension messaging and translation API origins as in `manifest.json`.
- **`img-src`**: follow manifest (e.g. `'self'`, `data:`, `https:` if needed for icons/images).
- When changing CSP, reload the extension and verify options **Theme** tab and any page using inline styles.

Security and Privacy:

- Treat CSP as part of the security model; prefer `'unsafe-inline'` only where needed (currently theme previews), and avoid widening `script-src`.
- Use HTTPS for all network requests
- Sanitize user inputs and validate data from external sources
- Implement proper error handling and logging

